The paper discusses the security and anonymity challenges in mobile ad hoc networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and computer networks (cs.NI). The proposed protocol involves distributed reputation management, which can also be categorized under distributed computing (cs.DC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The use of cryptography in the protocol implementation can be related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
